The paper deals with interference reduction in multi-cell massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of optimization techniques to design precoding methods also falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on downlink analysis for a finite number of antennas, which is a sub-topic of massive MIMO (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the proposed methods, which could be relevant to communication and networking (cs.COM).
